.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBpaping\fP is an open-source utility for testing TCP/IP network connectivity between hosts.
.PP
It works similarly to \fBping\fP(8), but uses TCP connections instead of ICMP echo requests.
This allows testing whether a remote host is reachable and whether a specific TCP port is accepting connections.
.PP
\fBpaping\fP can be useful for:
.PP
.nf
.fam C
 • testing service availability
 • troubleshooting firewall issues
 • measuring TCP connection response times
 • verifying remote port accessibility

.fam T
.fi
A successful TCP connection generally follows the TCP three-way handshake:
.PP
.nf
.fam C
 1) Client sends SYN
 2) Server replies with SYN, ACK
 3) Client sends ACK

.fam T
.fi
\fBpaping\fP measures the time required to establish the TCP connection and reports the result to the user.
